description.narrative: Immunization Evidence, Equity and FinancingGlobal and national policies in priority countries are based on evidence, addressing the immunization needs of the most disadvantaged children and women (Roadmap Outcome 1), which contributes to Immunization. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every Child to Survive and Thrive By 2021, countries apply child-sensitive policies, innovative community-centered approaches and evidence, to implement development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that enable Every Child to Survive and Thrive

description.narrative: By leading, co-convening and actively participating in the global immunization coordination and technical fora of the Immunization Agenda 2030 (IA2030) and Gavi, The Vaccine Alliance, UNICEF continued to advocate for equity-focused programming and for using the zero-dose agenda as an entry point for integrated service delivery as well as for Primary Health Care (PHC) strengthening. Strategic and deliberate efforts were made to support regions and countries in restoring and sustaining immunization coverage and in leveraging COVID-19 response investments for strengthening national immunization supply chains, demand for routine immunization and broader PHC. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/03/2022
